        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Method",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Make the tomato sauce",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oil in a saucepan over a medium heat. Add the onion and cook for 8 minutes until soft and lightly golden. Add the garlic and tomato puree and cook for 1 minute more.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the tinned tomatoes and oregano. Season with salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally, until the sauce is thick and slightly reduced.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 3
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cook the pasta and assemble",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "orderedList",
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Heat the oven to 200°C fan. Cook the pasta in well-salted boiling water for 2 minutes less than the packet says. It will finish cooking in the oven. Drain.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Add the pasta to the sauce and toss to coat well. Tip into a baking tin and smooth the top. Cover generously with the grated cheddar.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            },
            {
              "type": "listItem",
              "content": [
                {
                  "type": "paragraph",
                  "content": [
                    {
                      "text": "Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until the cheese is golden and bubbling and the edges of the pasta are beginning to crisp. Leave to rest for 5 minutes before serving.",
                      "type": "text"
                    }
                  ]
                }
              ]
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "troubleshooter",
          "attrs": {
            "items": [
              {
                "fix": "Add a splash of water or stock before topping with cheese next time. Cooking the pasta 2 minutes less than usual also prevents it drying out.",
                "cause": "The sauce was too thick before baking, or the pasta absorbed all the liquid.",
                "symptom": "The top is golden but the pasta inside is dry"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Move to the top shelf and give it another 5 to 8 minutes, watching closely.",
                "cause": "The oven was not hot enough, or the bake was on too low a shelf.",
                "symptom": "The cheese looks pale after baking"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Simmer the sauce for longer before adding the pasta. Taste and season boldly; pasta absorbs salt and needs the sauce to be slightly over-seasoned before baking.",
                "cause": "The tinned tomatoes were not cooked long enough, or insufficient salt was used.",
                "symptom": "The sauce tastes flat"
              },
              {
                "fix": "Cook 2 minutes less than the packet instructions. The pasta will finish in the oven.",
                "cause": "It was fully cooked before going in the oven.",
                "symptom": "The pasta is mushy"
              }
            ]
          }
        },
        {
          "type": "heading",
          "attrs": {
            "level": 2
          },
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Where this dish lives",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "paragraph",
          "content": [
            {
              "text": "Cheesy pasta bake sits alongside macaroni cheese and tuna pasta bake in the heartland of British family cooking. Speed and comfort are the only two requirements. It arrived with the tinned-tomato era. It uses things from the cupboard. It pleases almost everyone at the table.",
              "type": "text"
            }
          ]
        }
